race.comment: SWEETHEARTED (11) resumes. He's a talented gelding who hit the line well in a Listed race behind Alabama Lass at Flemington when fresh last campaign, eventually running fifth in a G2 Tobin Bronze behind subsequent G1 Goodwood winner Reserve Bank. They've lowered their sights here to a BM78 and while he needs things to go his way on the map, he'll be very hard to hold out. GRAND LARCENY (5) started favourite first up at Moonee Valley and was okay behind a dominant winner when third. Up to 1100m for the first time should be okay and he's got a nice profile with Shinn sticking. DON'T HOPE DO (4) is fresh for this and racing well. He should be right there again in an open race. JUST LIKE GABY (14) has always promised a bit and the first up win was in good company. She can go on with it now.
